This paper discusses the implementation of normative human-robot interactions in a cognitive robotic architecture, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in implementing these interactions. Additionally, the paper focuses on the social and moral norms that guide human behavior, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the potential use of this architecture in collaborative tasks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential use of machine learning algorithms in implementing these interactions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MA).
